{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:first-chronicles.2",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
    "chapterNumber": 2,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Chronicles 2 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:1",
      "text": "These are the sons of Israel: Reuben, Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Zebulun,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:2",
      "text": "Dan, Joseph, Benjamin, Naphtali, Gad, and Asher.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:3",
      "text": "The sons of Judah: Er, Onan, and Shelah, which three were born to him of Shua’s daughter the Canaanitess. Er, Judah’s firstborn, was wicked in Yahweh’s sight; and he killed him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:4",
      "text": "Tamar his daughter-in-law bore him Perez and Zerah. All the sons of Judah were five.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:5",
      "text": "The sons of Perez: Hezron and Hamul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:6",
      "text": "The sons of Zerah: Zimri, Ethan, Heman, Calcol, and Dara — five of them in all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:7",
      "text": "The son of Carmi: Achar, the troubler of Israel, who committed a trespass in the devoted thing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:8",
      "text": "The son of Ethan: Azariah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:9",
      "text": "The sons also of Hezron, who were born to him: Jerahmeel, Ram, and Chelubai.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:10",
      "text": "Ram became the father of Amminadab, and Amminadab became the father of Nahshon, prince of the children of Judah;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:11",
      "text": "and Nahshon became the father of Salma, and Salma became the father of Boaz,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:12",
      "text": "and Boaz became the father of Obed, and Obed became the father of Jesse;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:13",
      "text": "and Jesse became the father of his firstborn Eliab, Abinadab the second, Shimea the third,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:14",
      "text": "Nethanel the fourth, Raddai the fifth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:15",
      "text": "Ozem the sixth, and David the seventh;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:16",
      "text": "and their sisters were Zeruiah and Abigail. The sons of Zeruiah: Abishai, Joab, and Asahel, three.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:17",
      "text": "Abigail bore Amasa; and the father of Amasa was Jether the Ishmaelite.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:18",
      "text": "Caleb the son of Hezron became the father of children by Azubah his wife, and by Jerioth; and these were her sons: Jesher, Shobab, and Ardon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:19",
      "text": "Azubah died, and Caleb married Ephrath, who bore him Hur.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:20",
      "text": "Hur became the father of Uri, and Uri became the father of Bezalel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:21",
      "text": "Afterward Hezron went in to the daughter of Machir the father of Gilead, whom he took as wife when he was sixty years old; and she bore him Segub.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:22",
      "text": "Segub became the father of Jair, who had twenty-three cities in the land of Gilead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:23",
      "text": "Geshur and Aram took the towns of Jair from them, with Kenath, and its villages, even sixty cities. All these were the sons of Machir the father of Gilead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:24",
      "text": "After Hezron died in Caleb Ephrathah, Abijah, Hezron’s wife, bore him Ashhur the father of Tekoa.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:25",
      "text": "The sons of Jerahmeel the firstborn of Hezron were Ram the firstborn, Bunah, Oren, Ozem, and Ahijah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:26",
      "text": "Jerahmeel had another wife, whose name was Atarah. She was the mother of Onam.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:27",
      "text": "The sons of Ram the firstborn of Jerahmeel were Maaz, Jamin, and Eker.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:28",
      "text": "The sons of Onam were Shammai and Jada. The sons of Shammai: Nadab and Abishur.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:29",
      "text": "The name of the wife of Abishur was Abihail; and she bore him Ahban and Molid.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:30",
      "text": "The sons of Nadab: Seled and Appaim; but Seled died without children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:31",
      "text": "The son of Appaim: Ishi. The son of Ishi: Sheshan. The son of Sheshan: Ahlai.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:32",
      "text": "The sons of Jada the brother of Shammai: Jether and Jonathan; and Jether died without children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:33",
      "text": "The sons of Jonathan: Peleth and Zaza. These were the sons of Jerahmeel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:34",
      "text": "Now Sheshan had no sons, but only daughters. Sheshan had a servant, an Egyptian, whose name was Jarha.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:35",
      "text": "Sheshan gave his daughter to Jarha his servant as wife; and she bore him Attai.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.36",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:36",
      "text": "Attai became the father of Nathan, and Nathan became the father of Zabad,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.37",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:37",
      "text": "and Zabad became the father of Ephlal, and Ephlal became the father of Obed,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.38",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:38",
      "text": "and Obed became the father of Jehu, and Jehu became the father of Azariah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.39",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:39",
      "text": "and Azariah became the father of Helez, and Helez became the father of Eleasah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.40",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:40",
      "text": "and Eleasah became the father of Sismai, and Sismai became the father of Shallum,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.41",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:41",
      "text": "and Shallum became the father of Jekamiah, and Jekamiah became the father of Elishama.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.42",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:42",
      "text": "The sons of Caleb the brother of Jerahmeel were Mesha his firstborn, who was the father of Ziph, and the sons of Mareshah the father of Hebron.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.43",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:43",
      "text": "The sons of Hebron: Korah, Tappuah, Rekem, and Shema.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.44",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:44",
      "text": "Shema became the father of Raham, the father of Jorkeam; and Rekem became the father of Shammai.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.45",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:45",
      "text": "The son of Shammai was Maon; and Maon was the father of Beth Zur.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.46",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:46",
      "text": "Ephah, Caleb’s concubine, bore Haran, Moza, and Gazez; and Haran became the father of Gazez.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.47",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:47",
      "text": "The sons of Jahdai: Regem, Jothan, Geshan, Pelet, Ephah, and Shaaph.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.48",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:48",
      "text": "Maacah, Caleb’s concubine, bore Sheber and Tirhanah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.49",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:49",
      "text": "She bore also Shaaph the father of Madmannah, Sheva the father of Machbena and the father of Gibea; and the daughter of Caleb was Achsah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.50",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:50",
      "text": "These were the sons of Caleb, the son of Hur, the firstborn of Ephrathah: Shobal the father of Kiriath Jearim,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.51",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:51",
      "text": "Salma the father of Bethlehem, and Hareph the father of Beth Gader.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.52",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:52",
      "text": "Shobal the father of Kiriath Jearim had sons: Haroeh, half of the Menuhoth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.53",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:53",
      "text": "The families of Kiriath Jearim: the Ithrites, the Puthites, the Shumathites, and the Mishraites; from them came the Zorathites and the Eshtaolites.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.54",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 54,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:54",
      "text": "The sons of Salma: Bethlehem, the Netophathites, Atroth Beth Joab, and half of the Manahathites, the Zorites.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-chronicles.2.55",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 55,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:55",
      "text": "The families of scribes who lived at Jabez: the Tirathites, the Shimeathites, and the Sucathites. These are the Kenites who came from Hammath, the father of the house of Rechab.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
